race.comment: TEMPRANILLO (7) resumed over 1200m last time out and turned in a solid effort to finish second at Seymour. The extra journey should play into her hands. Likely to feature in the finish. PRAVAHA (10) is in one of the country's best juvenile stables and has prepped up nicely at the Flemington jumpouts. There was a lot to like about her most recent effort when she led all the way, which suggests she's capable of utilising the great barrier here. PRINCE OF BROOKY (4) has filled a minor placing at both runs this time in work and looks close to a maiden win, the latest effort a second over 1100m at Moe. Among the major players. AKA DAKA (1) comes through the same race at the favourite and has some ground to make up on that runner but no reason he can't again figure in the placings.
